=====短期影響=====
{{main|喝酒的短期影響}}
 
飲酒讓[[血液酒精濃度|血液酒精濃度]] (BAC) 達到0.03-0.12%的時候，通常會讓整體情緒改善，以及可能產生[[欣快|欣快]]的感覺、自信和社交能力增加、焦慮減少、[[酒精反應|臉紅反應]]、和判斷力及肌肉精細協調力受到妨礙。BAC增加到0.09%至0.25%的時候，會導致[[嗜睡|嗜睡]]、{{le|鎮靜|sedation}}、有平衡問題、和視力模糊。當BAC到達0.18%至0.30%的程度時，會導致極度混亂、言語障礙（例如口齒不清）、步態蹣跚、頭暈、和嘔吐。到0.25%至0.40%的時候，會導致{{le|木僵|stupor}}、意識不清、[[順行性遺忘症|順行性遺忘]]、嘔吐（失去知覺時因吸入嘔吐物，會因導致[[吸入性肺炎|吸入性肺炎]]而死亡）、和[[呼吸抑制|換氣不足]]（呼吸抑制，可能會危及生命）。濃度增加到0.35%到0.80%時會導致[[昏迷|昏迷]]（意識不清）、危及生命的呼吸抑制、以及可能致命的[[酒精中毒|酒精中毒]]。飲用酒精飲料後，在駕駛機動車輛、開飛機、或是操作重型機械都會增加發生事故的風險；對於[[酒後駕駛|酒後駕駛]]，許多國家均會給予處罰。

=====長期影響=====
{{see also|喝酒的長期影響}}
 
女性每天喝超過一份（[[英國|英國]]的一份相當於10毫升純[[乙醇|乙醇]]）），或男性每天喝兩份酒精，都會增加罹患[[心臟病|心臟病]]、[[高血壓|高血壓]]、[[心房顫動|心房顫動]]、以及[[中風|中風]]的風險。<ref name="Kee2014">{{cite journal|vauthors=O'Keefe JH, Bhatti SK, Bajwa A, DiNicolantonio JJ, Lavie CJ|date=March 2014|title=Alcohol and cardiovascular health: the dose makes the poison…or the remedy|journal=Mayo Clinic Proceedings|volume=89|issue=3|pages=382–93|doi=10.1016/j.mayocp.2013.11.005|pmid=24582196|doi-access=free}}</ref>暴飲的風險更大，也會導致暴力或事故的發生。而酒精使用是導致美國過早死亡的第三大原因。<ref name=Kee2014 />從來沒有專業的醫學協會會建議不飲酒的人該開始飲酒。<ref name=Kee2014 /><ref>[http://www.heart.org/HEARTORG/GettingHealthy/NutritionCenter/HealthyEating/Alcohol-and-Heart-Health_UCM_305173_Article.jsp ''Alcohol and Heart Health''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119121521/http://www.heart.org/HEARTORG/GettingHealthy/NutritionCenter/HealthyEating/Alcohol-and-Heart-Health_UCM_305173_Article.jsp |date=19 January 2016 }} American Heart Association</ref>長期濫用酒精會導致許多身體症狀發生，包括肝硬化、[[胰腺炎|胰臟炎]]、[[腦癇症|癲癇]]、{{le|多發性神經病變|polyneuropathy}}、韋尼克-科爾薩科夫症候群、心臟病、營養缺乏、[[胃及十二指腸潰瘍|胃及十二指腸潰瘍]]、<ref>{{cite book |last=American Medical Association |title=Complete Medical Encyclopedia|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=WGURAQAAMAAJ}} |year=2003|publisher=Random House Reference |location=New York |isbn=978-0-8129-9100-0|edition=First | chapter = Duodenal Ulcer | veditors = Leiken JS, Lipsky MS |page=485 }}</ref>和[[性功能障礙|性功能障礙]]，這些最終可能都會致命。其他對身體的影響包括罹患[[心血管疾病|心血管疾病]]、{{le|吸收不良|Malabsorption}}、[[酒精性肝病|酒精性肝病]]、還有和幾種癌症的風險會增加。持續飲酒會同時損害[[中樞神經系統|中樞神經系統]]和[[周圍神經系統|周圍神經系統]]。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Müller D, Koch RD, von Specht H, Völker W, Münch EM | title = [Neurophysiologic findings in chronic alcohol abuse] | language = de | journal = Psychiatrie, Neurologie, und Medizinische Psychologie | volume = 37 | issue = 3 | pages = 129–32 | date = March 1985 | pmid = 2988001 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Testino G | title = Alcoholic diseases in hepato-gastroenterology: a point of view | journal = Hepato-Gastroenterology | volume = 55 | issue = 82–83 | pages = 371–7 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18613369 }}</ref>可能會導致廣泛的免疫缺陷，除一般所知的容易受到意外傷害之外，還可能會有一般性骨骼脆弱狀況，而容易發生骨折。<ref>[http://pubs.niaaa.nih.gov/publications/10report/intro.pdf 10th Special Report to the U.S. Congress on Alcohol and Health] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120913074727/http://pubs.niaaa.nih.gov/publications/10report/intro.pdf |date=13 September 2012 }}, 2000, U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, Public Health Service National Institutes of Health, National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism.</ref>
 
有酒精依賴的女性比男性更快出現長期併發症狀。此外，酗酒女性的死亡率高於男性。<ref name="Blume Laura N., Nielson Nancy H., Riggs Joseph A., et all 1998 861–870"/>長期併發症包括有腦、心臟、和肝損傷，<ref name="Walter H., Gutierrez K., Ramskogler K., Hertling I., Dvorak A., Lesch O.M., et al. 2003 253–268" />以及罹患[[乳癌|乳癌]]的風險增加。此外，有證據顯示長期大量飲酒會對女性的[[生殖系統|生殖系統]]產生負面影響。會導致生殖功能障礙，例如{{le|不排卵|anovulation}}、卵巢體積減少、[[月經週期|月經週期]]出現問題或不規律、以及[[更年期|更年期]]提前發生。<ref name="Blume Laura N., Nielson Nancy H., Riggs Joseph A., et all 1998 861–870" />對於長期濫用酒精，且近期有暴飲史的人，可能會發生酒精性[[酮酸中毒|酮酸中毒]]。<ref name="Mihai-">{{cite journal | vauthors = Mihai B, Lăcătuşu C, Graur M | title = [Alcoholic ketoacidosis] | journal = Revista Medico-Chirurgicala a Societatii de Medici Si Naturalisti Din Iasi | volume = 112 | issue = 2 | pages = 321–6 | date = April–June 2008 | pmid = 19294998 }}</ref><ref name="Sibaï-2005">{{cite journal | vauthors = Sibaï K, Eggimann P | title = [Alcoholic ketoacidosis: not rare cause of metabolic acidosis] | journal = Revue Médicale Suisse | volume = 1 | issue = 32 | pages = 2106, 2108–10, 2112–5 | date = September 2005 | pmid = 16238232 }}</ref>不同的性別，有不同的代謝酒精，及處理酒精影響的能力。對於攝入等量酒精的男性和女性，通常是女性的血液酒精濃度會較高，因為女性的體重通常較低，體脂百分比較高，因此酒精的分佈容量會低於男性。<ref name="pmid23101976">{{cite journal | vauthors = Cederbaum AI | title = Alcohol metabolism | journal = Clinics in Liver Disease | volume = 16 | issue = 4 | pages = 667–85 | date = November 2012 | pmid = 23101976 | pmc = 3484320 | doi = 10.1016/j.cld.2012.08.002 }}</ref>

=====精神病學=====
長期濫用酒精會導致廣泛的[[心理衛生|心理健康]]問題發生。很常見的是嚴重的認知問題；大約有10%的[[失智症|失智症]]與飲酒有關，讓酒精成為導致失智症的第二大原因。<ref name="aamaibnc">{{Cite web |url=http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2008-07/econ-ma070808.php |title=Alcoholism-associated molecular adaptations in brain neurocognitive circuits | vauthors = Bakalkin G |date=2008-07-08 |website=Eurekalert.org |access-date=2012-01-11 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111130152434/http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2008-07/econ-ma070808.php |archive-date=2011-11-30  }}</ref>過量飲酒會導致[[腦損傷|腦損傷]]，長期而言，對於心理健康會產生日漸增大的影響。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Oscar-Berman M, Marinkovic K | title = Alcoholism and the brain: an overview | journal = Alcohol Research & Health | volume = 27 | issue = 2 | pages = 125–33 | year = 2003 | pmid = 15303622 | pmc = 6668884 }}</ref>由於酒精的[[神經毒性|神經毒性]]會對大腦（尤其對[[前額葉皮質|前額葉皮質]]）產生作用，酗酒者的{{le|社交技能|Social skills}}會顯著的受到損害。 受酒精使用疾患影響到的社交技能包括感知面部情緒表達、[[韻律_(語言學)|韻律]]（即說話者語言透露的情緒）、感知問題、和[[心智理論|心智理論]]方面的缺陷；有酒精濫用問題的人對幽默的理解能力也會受損。<ref name="pmid18412750">{{cite journal | vauthors = Uekermann J, Daum I | title = Social cognition in alcoholism: a link to prefrontal cortex dysfunction? | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_british-journal-of-addiction_2008-05_103_5/page/726 | journal = Addiction | volume = 103 | issue = 5 | pages = 726–35 | date = May 2008 | pmid = 18412750 | doi = 10.1111/j.1360-0443.2008.02157.x }}</ref>有酒精使用疾患的人之中罹患[[精神疾患|精神疾患]]很常見，其中有多達25%的人症狀屬於嚴重類型。精神症狀中最普遍的是焦慮症和[[抑鬱症|抑鬱症]]。在酒精戒斷症狀初期，精神症狀通常會惡化，但通常會因持續戒酒而改善或是消失。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Wetterling T, Junghanns K | title = Psychopathology of alcoholics during withdrawal and early abstinence | journal = European Psychiatry | volume = 15 | issue = 8 | pages = 483–8 | date = December 2000 | pmid = 11175926 | doi = 10.1016/S0924-9338(00)00519-8 | s2cid = 24094651 }}</ref>[[精神症|精神症]]、{{le|混餚|confusion}}、和{{le|器質性腦症候群|organic brain syndrome}}可能是由酒精濫用所引起，這可能會導致誤診為[[精神分裂症|精神分裂症]]。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Schuckit MA | title = Alcoholism and other psychiatric disorders | journal = Hospital & Community Psychiatry | volume = 34 | issue = 11 | pages = 1022–7 | date = November 1983 | pmid = 6642446 | doi = 10.1176/ps.34.11.1022 }}</ref>長期濫用酒精會直接導致[[恐慌症|恐慌症]]的發生或是惡化。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Cowley DS | title = Alcohol abuse, substance abuse, and panic disorder | journal = The American Journal of Medicine | volume = 92 | issue = 1A | pages = 41S–48S | date = January 1992 | pmid = 1346485 | doi = 10.1016/0002-9343(92)90136-Y }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Cosci F, Schruers KR, Abrams K, Griez EJ | title = Alcohol use disorders and panic disorder: a review of the evidence of a direct relationship | journal = The Journal of Clinical Psychiatry | volume = 68 | issue = 6 | pages = 874–80 | date = June 2007 | pmid = 17592911 | doi = 10.4088/JCP.v68n0608 }}</ref>
 
[[重性抑鬱疾患|重度抑鬱]]和酗酒同時發生有翔實的記錄可查。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Grant BF, Harford TC | title = Comorbidity between DSM-IV alcohol use disorders and major depression: results of a national survey | journal = Drug and Alcohol Dependence | volume = 39 | issue = 3 | pages = 197–206 | date = October 1995 | pmid = 8556968 | doi = 10.1016/0376-8716(95)01160-4 | url = https://zenodo.org/record/1258497 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Kandel DB, Huang FY, Davies M | title = Comorbidity between patterns of substance use dependence and psychiatric syndromes | journal = Drug and Alcohol Dependence | volume = 64 | issue = 2 | pages = 233–41 | date = October 2001 | pmid = 11543993 | doi = 10.1016/S0376-8716(01)00126-0 | author-link1 = Denise Kandel }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | vauthors = Cornelius JR, Bukstein O, Salloum I, Clark D | title = Recent Developments in Alcoholism | chapter = Alcohol and psychiatric comorbidity | journal = Recent Dev Alcohol | volume = 16 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/recentdevelopment00gala/page/361 361–74] | year = 2003 | pmid = 12638646 | doi = 10.1007/0-306-47939-7_24 | chapter-url = https://archive.org/details/recentdevelopment00gala/page/361 | isbn = 978-0-306-47258-9 | issn = 0738-422X | series = Recent Developments in Alcoholism | publisher = Kluwer Academic/Plenum Publishers }}</ref>在那些有[[共病症|共病症]]的患者中，抑鬱發作通常可分為因戒酒而發生（“物質誘發”），還有原發性，並非因戒酒而發生（“獨立”發作）。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Schuckit MA, Tipp JE, Bergman M, Reich W, Hesselbrock VM, Smith TL | title = Comparison of induced and independent major depressive disorders in 2,945 alcoholics | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-psychiatry_1997-07_154_7/page/948 | journal = The American Journal of Psychiatry | volume = 154 | issue = 7 | pages = 948–57 | date = July 1997 | pmid = 9210745 | doi = 10.1176/ajp.154.7.948 | doi-access = free }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Schuckit MA, Tipp JE, Bucholz KK, Nurnberger JI, Hesselbrock VM, Crowe RR, Kramer J | title = The life-time rates of three major mood disorders and four major anxiety disorders in alcoholics and controls | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_british-journal-of-addiction_1997-10_92_10/page/1289 | journal = Addiction | volume = 92 | issue = 10 | pages = 1289–304 | date = October 1997 | pmid = 9489046 | doi = 10.1111/j.1360-0443.1997.tb02848.x | s2cid = 14958283 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Schuckit MA, Smith TL, Danko GP, Pierson J, Trim R, Nurnberger JI, Kramer J, Kuperman S, Bierut LJ, Hesselbrock V | display-authors = 6 | title = A comparison of factors associated with substance-induced versus independent depressions | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-studies-on-alcohol-and-drugs_2007-11_68_6/page/805 | journal = Journal of Studies on Alcohol and Drugs | volume = 68 | issue = 6 | pages = 805–12 | date = November 2007 | pmid = 17960298 | doi = 10.15288/jsad.2007.68.805 | s2cid = 17528609 }}</ref>除酒精之外，額外使用到其他藥物可能會增加罹患抑鬱症的風險。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Schuckit M | title = Alcoholic patients with secondary depression | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-psychiatry_1983-06_140_6/page/711 | journal = The American Journal of Psychiatry | volume = 140 | issue = 6 | pages = 711–4 | date = June 1983 | pmid = 6846629 | doi = 10.1176/ajp.140.6.711 }}</ref>精神障礙的發生因性別而異。患有酒精使用疾患的女性通常同時患有精神疾病，例如重度抑鬱、焦慮症、恐慌症、[[神經性爆食症|神經性爆食症]]、[[創傷後壓力症候群|創傷後壓力症候群]] (PTSD) 、或[[邊緣性人格障礙|邊緣性人格障礙]]。患有酒精使用疾患的男性通常會同時患有[[自戀型人格疾患|自戀型人格疾患]]或[[反社會人格障礙|反社會人格障礙]]、[[躁鬱症|躁鬱症]]、精神分裂症、[[衝動控制障礙|衝動控制障礙]]、或[[注意力不足過動症|注意力不足過動症]] (ADHD)。<ref name="Karrol_2002">{{Cite journal| vauthors = Karrol BR |s2cid=73186615 | name-list-style = vanc |title=Women and alcohol use disorders: a review of important knowledge and its implications for social work practitioners | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_british-journal-of-social-work_2002-04_32_3/page/337 |journal=Journal of Social Work |volume=2 |issue=3 |pages=337–56 |year=2002 |doi=10.1177/146801730200200305 }}</ref>
 
與一般的女性相比，患有酒精使用疾患的女性更容易遭到身體侵犯或是[[性侵犯|性侵犯]]、虐待、和[[家庭暴力|家庭暴力]]，<ref name="Karrol_2002" />反過來，這又可能導致更多的精神障礙和酒精依賴發生。

=====社會影響=====
{{see also|{{le|與毒品有關的犯罪|Drug-related crime}}}}
 
酒精使用疾患會引起嚴重的社會問題；這些困境是由大腦的病理變化和酒精中毒所引起。<ref name="aamaibnc"/><ref name="Jessica Kingsley Publishers"/>酒精濫用會增加刑事罪行發生，包括[[虐待兒童|虐待兒童]]、家庭暴力、[[強姦|強姦]]、{{le|入室盜竊|burglary}}、和攻擊他人等風險。<ref name="drug_use_a_reference_handbook">{{Cite book| last1 = Isralowitz | first1 = Richard | name-list-style = vanc | title = Drug use: a reference handbook | url = {{google books |plainurl=y |id=X0mxxfbIbp4C}} | year = 2004 | publisher = ABC-CLIO | location = Santa Barbara, CA | isbn = 978-1-57607-708-5 | pages = 122–23}}</ref>酗酒與遭受{{le|解僱|Termination of employment}}（而產生財務問題）有關聯。<ref>{{Cite book| last1 = Langdana | first1 = Farrokh K. | name-list-style = vanc | title = Macroeconomic Policy: Demystifying Monetary and Fiscal Policy | url = {{google books |plainurl=y |id=GCYWQn79JYwC}} | year=2009 | publisher = Springer | edition = 2nd | isbn = 978-0-387-77665-1 | page = 81 }}</ref>在不恰當的時間飲酒，和在缺乏判斷力而做出的行為，可能會導致觸犯法律的後果，例如酒後駕駛、<ref name="abd2009">{{Cite book| last1 = Gifford | first1 = Maria | name-list-style = vanc | title = Alcoholism (Biographies of Disease) | year=2009 | publisher = Greenwood Press | url = {{google books |plainurl=y |id=2OJV12astRUC|page=89}} | isbn = 978-0-313-35908-8 | pages = 89–91 }}</ref>違反公共秩序，或發生[[侵權行為|侵權行為]]而受到民事處罰。酗酒者在醉酒時發生的行為以及精神障礙會對其周圍的人造成深遠的影響，而造成與家人和朋友間的疏離。這種疏離情況會導致{{le|關係疾患|relational disorder}}以及[[離婚|離婚]]，或導致家庭暴力。酗酒還會導致{{le|兒童忽視|Child neflect}}，從而對有使用疾患患者的子女，在他們的情緒發展上造成長遠的傷害。<ref name="tcemh2006">{{Cite book |last1=Schadé |first1=Johannes Petrus | name-list-style = vanc |title=The Complete Encyclopedia of Medicine and Health |year=2006 |publisher=Foreign Media Books |url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=j8DuEHxSCU4C|page=132}} |isbn=978-1-60136-001-4 |pages=132–33 }}</ref>出於這種原因，有使用疾患患者的子女可能會出現許多情緒上的問題。例如，子女會因父母不穩定的情緒，而心生恐懼。而子女可能因自己無力將父母從酗酒中解救，而心生羞恥感，繼而產生[[自我形象|自我形象]]問題，導致抑鬱的發生。<ref>{{cite web |last=Gold |first=Mark | name-list-style = vanc |title=Children of Alcoholics |url=http://psychcentral.com/lib/2006/children-of-alcoholics/ |publisher=Psych Central |access-date=2011-11-27 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111116010950/http://psychcentral.com/lib/2006/children-of-alcoholics/ |archive-date=2011-11-16 }}</ref>
 
