酗酒通常會把人的[[預期壽命|預期壽命]]縮短十年左右。<ref name=Schu2014/>最常見的酗酒者死亡原因是心血管併發症。<ref name="Zuskin-2006">{{cite journal | vauthors = Zuskin E, Jukić V, Lipozencić J, Matosić A, Mustajbegović J, Turcić N, Poplasen-Orlovac D, Bubas M, Prohić A | display-authors = 6 | title = [Alcoholism--how it affects health and working capacity] | journal = Arhiv Za Higijenu Rada I Toksikologiju | volume = 57 | issue = 4 | pages = 413–26 | date = December 2006 | pmid = 17265681 }}</ref>長期酗酒者的[[自殺|自殺]]率很高，飲酒史越長，自殺率就會越高。大約有3-15%的酗酒者會自殺，<ref>{{cite book|title=American Psychiatric Association practice guidelines for the treatment of psychiatric disorders|date=2006|publisher=American Psychiatric Association|location=Arlington, VA|isbn=978-0-89042-385-1|page=1346|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=zql0AqtRSrYC|page=1346}}|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529103328/https://books.google.com/books?id=zql0AqtRSrYC&pg=PA1346|archive-date=2016-05-29}}</ref>研究發現，超過50%的自殺與酒精或藥物依賴有關。這被認為是由於酒精導致大腦化學的生理變化以及社會孤立。在青少年酗酒者中自殺也很常見，25%的青少年自殺與酗酒有關。<ref name="understanding_suicidal_behaviour_a02">{{Cite book| last1 = O'Connor | first1 = Rory | last2 = Sheehy | first2 = Noel | name-list-style = vanc | title = Understanding suicidal behaviour | url = {{google books |plainurl=y |id=79hEYGdDA3oC}} | date = 2000-01-29 | publisher = BPS Books | location = Leicester | isbn = 978-1-85433-290-5 | pages = 33–37 }}</ref>成為酒精依賴者一年後，有人維持低危飲酒的標準，但只有25.5%的人接受治療。這個群組可細分為：25%的人仍有酒精依賴問題、27.3%的人處於部分緩解（仍有某些症存在）、11.8%的無症狀飲酒者（飲酒會把復發機會拉高）、和35.9%的完全康復（包含17.7%的低風險飲酒者和18.2%的戒酒者）。 <ref name="NIAAA2002">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nih.gov/news/pr/jan2005/niaaa-18.htm |title=2001–2002 Survey Finds That Many Recover From Alcoholism |last1=The National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism |last2=U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, NIH News |date=2005-01-18 |publisher=National Institutes of Health |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060818230335/http://www.nih.gov/news/pr/jan2005/niaaa-18.htm |archive-date=2006-08-18 }}</ref>相較之下，針對兩組酗酒男性的長期（60年）隨訪結果顯示，“回復到有節制的飲酒很少能持續超過十年，或者就是復發，或者就演變成完全戒酒。”<ref name="VAILLANT2003"/>還有“如同短期研究報告，想回復到有節制的飲酒，其可能性通常是海市蜃樓，不易達成。”。
 
